<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis box="[197,303,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks</emphasis>
. The epicnemial carina is difficult to see in the available specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1213,1356,1505,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Physotarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabellus">
<emphasis box="[1213,1356,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. glabellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was therefore run to two different places in the key.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,152,1647]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The species name is derived from Latin and refers to the small body with greatly reduced setae. This species is known only from east-central 
<collectingCountry box="[623,699,1621,1647]" name="Brazil" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
